<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>98<percent/> of 50</li> 
<li>40<percent/> of 127</li> 
<li>1<percent/> of 2024</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 40<percent/> of 127</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{98}\%\cdot{50}={49}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{40}\%\cdot{127}={50.8}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1}\%\cdot{2024}={20.24}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 40<percent/> of 127 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>